  "prompt": "How can I start a hedge fund?",
  "response": "Starting a hedge fund involves several key steps:\n\n1. Educational Requirements\n- Advanced degree (finance, economics)\n- Investment management credentials\n- Strong financial background\n\n2. Professional Qualifications\n- Series 7 and Series 63 licenses\n- Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA) certification helpful\n\n3. Business Planning\n- Develop clear investment strategy\n- Define target market/investors\n- Create detailed business plan\n- Determine fund structure\n\n4. Legal and Regulatory Compliance\n- Register with SEC\n- Establish legal entity (LLC or partnership)\n- Comply with investment regulations\n- Get necessary licenses\n\n5. Capital Requirements\n- Minimum initial capital ($500,000 - $1 million typically)\n- Personal investment or seed funding\n- Potential outside investors\n\n6. Infrastructure\n- Trading platforms\n- Risk management systems\n- Back-office operations\n- Compliance monitoring\n\n7. Marketing and Fundraising\n- Build investor network\n- Create marketing materials\n- Develop investor relations strategy\n\n8. Operational Considerations\n- Hire experienced staff\n- Select prime broker\n- Establish accounting/reporting systems\n- Set up performance tracking\n\n9. Ongoing Management\n- Consistent performance\n- Transparent reporting\n- Risk management\n- Continuous strategy refinement\n\nProfessional guidance is recommended throughout this process.",
